node.text:
In season 2, episode 3 of Leo's Learnings, Leo interviews HOKA ONE ONE Northern Arizona Elite standout @danishani. Throughout their discussion, Leo and Dani discuss Dani's early season success on the track, how injury derailed her strong season, and what she's doing now to stay injury-free, while also working on her mental approach to training. 
 
Leo also delves into how runners can handle injury, as well as how to incorporate injury prevention techniques in your weekly training routines. Lastly, he talks about the HOKA ONE ONE Summer Mile Club. Learn more about the HOKA ONE ONE Summer Mile Club, how to join, what amazing HOKA perks you can earn, and more at http://www.hokasummermileclub.com.

Watch the full episode at runnerspace.com or link in our bio

node.text:
In episode 10 of Leo's Learnings, @leomanzano interviews @rachschneid18, who will represent the United States at the Olympic Games in Tokyo. Over the course of the interview, Schneider breaks down her Olympic Trials experience, how her mindset has shifted over the past five years, practicing patience as an athlete, summer training tips, and much more.
 
Leo also shares his insights on practicing patience during training, both in the short-term and long-term. Lastly, he talks about the @hokaoneone Summer Mile Club. Learn more about the #HOKASummerMileClub, how to join, what amazing HOKA perks you can earn, and more at http://www.hokasummermileclub.com.

Hosted by two-time Olympian and all-around good guy Leo Manzano, Leo's Learnings gives viewers an entertaining and informative look at the professional side of the sport. Through guest interviews with athletes and influencers, offering training tips, and issuing challenges, Leo's Learnings is a must-watch for any fan of track and field.

Watch full show here: https://www.dyestat.com/gprofile.php?mgroup_id=44531&do=videos&video_id=308130-Leo-039-s-Learnings-Episode-10-Rachel-Schneider

node.text:
Welcome to the #BrooksPR Challenge Medal Ceremony for June 2021 where we celebrate some of the top PRs set on Athletic.net for the past month!

Plus watch the Brooks PR Invite LIVE at 2pm PT on July 2nd! Link in @runnerspace bio.

Sifan Hassan is chasing the women’s 5000m world record Friday night at the @preclassic but she’s got company! 

Tell us who’s winning this race + her winning time and you’ll win a year of RunnerSpace +PLUS!
⠀
Example: 

Entries:
🇳🇱 Sifan HASSAN	
🇪🇹 Fantu WORKU

🇲🇽 Laura GALVAN	
🇰🇪 Beatrice CHEBET	
🇨🇦 Kate VAN BUSKIRK	
🇰🇪 Loice CHEMNUNG	

Watch Friday night’s Distance Night in Eugene at the @preclassic LIVE on @usatf TV+ (link in bio). More meet info at preclassic.com.

Rules: Entries are due by Friday, August 20 at 5PM PT. Only 1 entry per account. If you submit more than 1 entry the 1st one will be used. Whoever picks the correct winning athlete will be declared the winner. In the event of a tie because no entry matches the correct athlete, whoever is closest to the winning athlete’s time without being slower than the actual time is declared the winner. If we still have a tie whoever posted the correct entry first will be declared the winner. The winner will be announced in the comment section of this post by Sunday, August 22.⠀

⠀
